    {
      "id": "a2b0dcc1604ff924ec4d63d63b5d2c0f5804baf3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 292,
        "name": "James Nunez",
        "email": "jnunez@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jnunez"
      },
      "date": "2019-08-14 14:50:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nPatrick - Should we increase the barrier time only for ZFS or do we want to increase the time for ldiskfs also? Right now, this fix is for both file systems.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0746f5b17ad3af92a57d2fdf51baeba4dfe79453",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-08-14 14:54:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nGood point - It is unnecessary for ldiskfs and it will cost us some extra time in testing.\n\nDo you mind making the change?  I'm juggling at the moment.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "3428bdc75a70002c17e606cf4d8bfcf1c5e15070",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 337,
        "name": "Li Xi",
        "email": "lixi@ddn.com",
        "username": "LiX"
      },
      "date": "2019-08-14 15:16:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> It is unnecessary for ldiskfs and it will cost us some extra time in testing.\n\nThis might be fine for ldiskfs? Because if the barrier freeze finishes quickly, it will return immediately and won't wait for 20 seconds. And I guess the sync on ldiskfs in VM environment still has the possibility of exceeding 5 seconds? So increase the timeout would reduce the possibility of test failure on ldiskfs too...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "fe151f8f5860cdbf8fff32437e9a3cf9ff30ff20",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 797,
        "name": "Patrick Farrell",
        "email": "pfarrell@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "pfarrell",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2019-08-14 15:27:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLi Xi,\n\nI actually don't know the answer - I thought the commit interval *was* 10 seconds.  What I know is it seemed to be taking 10 seconds in the logs, but I might be confused and it's 2 syncs.\n\nThanks for pointing out this should be fine for ldiskfs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
